headline: Coca-Cola forecasts sluggish revenue growth in 2026
summary:
STORY: Coca-Cola on Tuesday missed Wall Street expectations for fourth-quarter revenue.

It also forecast muted growth for 2026, as demand weakened in North America and Asia.

The news sent its shares down about 4% in premarket trading.

The company has been raising prices for its beverages to offset higher input costs.

But it comes at a time when U.S. consumers are increasingly looking for cheaper options as inflation squeezes budgets.

Rival PepsiCo said last week it would cut prices on key snacks such as Lay's and Doritos.

Consumers had pushed back against several rounds of price hikes over the last few years.

Coca-Cola expects 2026 organic revenue to grow 4% to 5%, compared with a 5% rise last year.

The company reported fourth-quarter revenue of $11.82 billion, missing estimates of just over $12 billion.
